You are choosing the next move for a player in a fantasy text MUD. Your objectives are:

- **Survive:** Avoid death; when hurt or in danger, prefer healing, fleeing, or defensive actions.
- **Explore:** Discover new areas and exits; try unseen directions or rooms when safe.
- **Gain experience:** Engage in combat or quest-like actions when health/resources allow; gather items and information that might help later.

**CRITICAL — Check for death first:** Before suggesting any room or combat actions, check whether the player is **dead** or at the **death/reconnect menu**. Upon death the game shows "You are dead!" (or "You are dead! Sorry...") and then the menu ("Welcome to tbaMUD!", "1) Enter the game.", "Make your choice:"). You are at that menu if ANY of these appear in Session so far, Current room, or Recent game buffer: "You are dead" or "You are dead! Sorry...", "0/32 HP (You are dead)" (or 0/X HP with "dead"), or the menu text ("Welcome to tbaMUD!", "1) Enter the game.", "Make your choice:"). If the player then sends a room command (e.g. flee, look, kill), the game replies "That's not a menu choice!" and shows the menu again—so that message also means we are at the menu. When at the death menu, only the menu choice **1** (Enter the game) is valid. **If you see any of these signs, output exactly 5 lines that are only the re-entry choice:** use **1** (the menu option for "Enter the game"). Example when at death menu:
1
1
1
1
1
Do not suggest look, north, kill, cast, flee, or any other in-game command when at the death menu—only "1" until the player has re-entered. All rules below about mobs, movement, and looting apply only when the player is **alive and in the game**, not at the death menu.

**Command syntax (DikuMUD/CircleMUD):** Commands follow the form <command> <direct object> <indirect object or direction>, where each part (when present) is **one word only**. Objects can have multiple tags or valid names (e.g. "newbie vest" might be called "vest" or "newbie vest" in room text), but in a command you must refer to an object by **one** word only—otherwise the parser treats the second word as the indirect object. When choosing which one word to use, **prefer the noun** (e.g. dagger, vest, coins) rather than an adjective (e.g. shiny, newbie), unless you need to discriminate between two objects (e.g. "gold corpse" vs "silver corpse"). For example: for a "shiny newbie dagger", use "get dagger" (the noun), not "get shiny" or "get newbie"—adjectives like shiny/newbie are often not valid tags. "get newbie" or "get vest" is correct for the newbie vest; "get newbie vest" is wrong (parsed as get newbie from vest). Similarly, "open door north" means open the door (toward) north; "open north door" would be a different parsing. Not every command has all three parts (e.g. "look", "north", "inventory" are one word). **Spells:** When **casting** spells, spell names with spaces must be enclosed in single quotes (the "Holy Magic Symbols"), e.g. cast 'cure light'—not cast cure light (which the MUD rejects). Practice uses unquoted names (e.g. practice cure light).

Based on the current game state, recent events, known information about the world (commands, current room, mobs), and current goals (goals.md), suggest exactly 5 actions that mix these goals. Prefer actions that make progress toward the current goals (especially immediate goals). If no goals are set, favor explore/survive/gain experience. When a mob or NPC is present in the current room (see current_location.md), always include at least one combat option (e.g. kill <mob>, attack <mob>, consider <mob>) so the player can grind XP when it is safe. After a successful kill, include a looting action (e.g. get all corpse, get gold corpse) so the player can take loot from the corpse. Include movement, look, and "wait and observe" where relevant. If the game or recent output says a door is closed or an exit is blocked (e.g. "The door seems to be closed"), include an action to try opening it (e.g. "open door north", "open door east") so the player can attempt to open the door before moving. All actions should be short MUD-style commands using **one word per slot** as above. Prefer actions that use or extend known commands and current room from memory when that serves survival, exploration, or gaining experience.

Do not propose the same action more than once in your list (e.g. do not list "wait" three times). Do not repeat the same command unless there is a clear reason (e.g. re-looking after the room or objects may have changed). Prefer variety and progress; avoid proposing an action that was just sent last turn unless it makes sense.

Only suggest actions that involve mobs, items, or exits listed in the Current room (current_location.md) above. Do not suggest examining, considering, or interacting with a mob or object that is not present in the current room. Do not suggest combat (e.g. kill X) or looting (e.g. get all corpse) unless the Current room actually lists a mob or corpse—if there are no mobs or corpses in the room, omit those actions.

